                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Does it make you better? No.  Does it make you worse? No.  Does it make you different? YES!
<br />

<br />
**the below observations are referring to the real chanters, not the buff bots being leveled to cast kei and is meant to be taken in a general sense, not specific**
<br />

<br />
In older days (pre-PoP / pre-SoL) chanters would focus on crowd control, buffing and debuffing.  There were times we might sit LFG for hours waiting for a spot to open up because it was too hard to solo, or we didn't know how to solo.  We grouped and most learned to do it well.  Most groups weren't ready to do anything unless there was a chanter in the group.
<br />

<br />
Today's chanter leveling up focuses on charming, and learns tactics for LDoN adventures.  They are not afraid to charm or solo and probably know how to do it better.  Chanters are no longer a needed class for a group and many will go without and not have any clue how to work with a chanter.
<br />

<br />
Is one better than the other?  NO!
<br />

<br />
I have seen friends start chanters and watched them level.  I have grouped with them playing alts.  They learned the skills needed for what they are doing.  However, just as many of the old-school chanters didn't learn to charm until high levels, the new chanters don't have the same huge pull management skills and mana management skills.  I have picked up tricks watching young chanters who have figured out some aspect of the class and have offered others that they have not thought of.  That is what makes places like The Runes so helpful and great.  There are many people here from all variety of backgrounds willing to share their experiences and knowledge with each other.  I don't see your post as a rant, but more of a comentary.  It speaks of the play conditions of a younger chanter and shows how things have changed.  When I was leveling LoIO, Guk, Seb, etc were busy places with many people.  Now it is difficult to find groups in any of the old zones where some loot (cash or items) can drop.
<br />

<br />
Do I still learn things about being a chanter?  Yes, on a regular basis.  When there is nothing left for me to learn as a chanter will be the day I delete Fadnae.  Do I teach more tricks or offer more advise than I learn? Yes, I have seen and done many things other chanters haven't.  My methods tend to be different from others I know.  I didn't know of any place like this to get strategies or advise and had no higher level chanters around that I could talk with as I was leveling.  Most of what I know I taught myself or developed with friends or in pickup groups.  Heck, most of the higher level enchanters I knew when I was leveling up didn't know as much about the class as I did.  I truely believe the same can and is true for those young chanters today who really desire to learn their role and what they can do.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=398646" target="_blank" class="postlink">Fadnae Vantempla</a>
<br />
The wicked...err..."good" witch with the <a href="http://www.ashenvendetta.com" target="_blank" class="postlink">Ashen Vendetta</a>
<br />
