                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Like it or not, the average quality of today's player is lower.  Even for those of us that are old school, the softness and easiness of today's game has tarnished our own skills.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Internet guides, mudflation in the bazaar, the availability of buffs in PoK (I was level 30 before I purchased PoP -- doh!), and maps all make the early levels easier, but does it make up for the things that make it harder? More importantly, does it make for a poorer player? Not in my experience...</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody"> 
<br />

<br />
An enchanter's skill comes from experience, from practice, from being in the chaos.  That chaos has been removed from most of the levelling game.  Because of people believing that they had to have enchanters in RoK, the gameplay for enchanters got killed  in SoV and it's never recovered.  You can still choose to seek it out, but most people do not.  That is what makes poorer players.  Not maps.  Not buffs.  Not mudflation.  Outdoor zones, single pulls, these dumbed us down.
<br />

<br />
Now, you may be an above average enchanter today.  You might be up there with the top enchanters of your server.  That's certainly possible...there's a lot of newer players that are good, even great.  And on the opposite side, back then, there were poor players as well.  But the average quality...it was higher.  If you'd played back then, you'd feel the same way.  
<br />

<br />
RoK truly was the height of the enchanter class and, in my opinion, the height of the game.  It's been downhill ever since, although LDoN is at last a slight step up.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
