                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Well, I started playing in July of 1999.  Somethings are easier these days.  The main things being that gear is cheap and exp is faster.  Level 59 took most of the people I knew 2-3 months to get through.
<br />

<br />
There are reasons people didn't use charm before.  
<br />
-One is that people at that point didn't really understand how important hps were to a caster.  Out of ignorance most enchanters were a lot wimpier than they are today.
<br />
-The biggest reason (IMHO) was the way pets used to work.  It used to be that pets broke mez.  And when I say they broke mez... I mean they broke mez all day long.  Pets also wandered off because of bad pathing and would agro mobs and wipe the group or raid.  These are the reasons that people hated grouping with pet classes and the reason that nobody used there animations past level 20 or so.  A Dire Charm pet (if they were around back then) with the old pet rules would end up killing you much more than a hasted, duel wielding pet does now.
<br />
There were people who charmed solo'd before kunark, they just didn't use it in group.
<br />
I generally only used charm as a form of crowd control versus giants.
<br />

<br />
It's not that being a newer player makes you bad, it's that the game has evolved to the point that bad players can still enjoy the game and advance.
<br />

<br />
Personally, I have no desire for a 3 hour corpse run followed up by 4 hours of experience work to regain what I lost.  I've been there and don't particularly want to go back.
<br />

<br />
LDoN has some elements that are easier than old school dungeons, but in some cases they are harder.  
<br />

<br />
LDoN dungeons are harder than going into some overcamped old world dungeon that you can walk around freely because every mob is claimed the instant it spawns.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
