                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">The game is easier now for a wide variety of reasons but there is one reason that has only been lightly touched upon. Player Knowledge.
<br />

<br />
The player next to you is probably someones alt who already knows alot about the game and how to work in group. This can make the life of a newer player much easier in many ways. This and the availablity of good gear/buffs can and does produce players of lesser ability. Does this mean any and all who started recently are poorer players? No, but it does mean that  newer players have an easier time leveling.
<br />

<br />
The game was harder pre-sol,sorry thats just a fact. It was made easier so that they could attract and keep more (paying) players. Hell levels* ,for example, were taken out due to people complaining that they made the game too hard. The original developers said they were the result of a mathmatical error but I don't think so, they were there to make the game more challenging but away they went so people could level faster. The original developers wanted a good challenging game, SOE wanted a cash cow.
<br />

<br />
* Levels 35,40,45,50, 55, and 59 used to take a lot more exp to work through. A mob that gave you half a blue of exp in a non-hell level would only give you a pixels worth of exp in a hell-level. For a good player they were a hurdle, for a bad player they were mountains.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Geaine Goldenspell
<br />
SoF-Prexus</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
