                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I'm a weird hybrid of the two types of Enchanters people have mentioned here.
<br />

<br />
I played an Enchanter a couple years ago -- got him to 47 -- and learned huge pull management, the value of PBAE stuns, mana management (back in the days before KEI existed and I never got high level enough to enjoy Theft of Thought), and such in places like Kaesora, pre Thul Tae Ew Cazic Thule, Lower Guk, and Chardok.
<br />

<br />
I learned my trade from some of Terris Thule's finest Enchanters, almost all of whom are now 65 with gobs of AA, asking a couple questions but mostly just by watching them work their magic while playing my Ranger (who was my main at the time) in places like Sebilis, Charasis, Royals area Chardok, Kael Drakkal, and the Temple of Veeshan.
<br />

<br />
Then I deleted all my characters and quit EQ for what I thought was for good.
<br />

<br />
That lasted just over a year. <img src="images/smiles/icon_wink.gif" alt="icon_wink.gif" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
When I came back, I made another Enchanter (Provender) and have gotten him to 58 primarily through charm soloing (in Mistmoore, Kaesora, and Torgiran Mines) and LDoN adventures.  Things have changed a lot; Pacify actually works now, and people are sadly addicted to KEI and routinely break mezzes and run for zone/cry for evac if there are more than 3 in camp.
<br />

<br />
I have avoided PoP, because Enchanters are nigh useless in Tier 2/3 zones, and there are rarely any groups in Tier 1 (except boring PoJ exit groups).  I don't feel like charm soloing in Tier 1, because I felt like what drove me away from EQ in the first place was how boring and lonely soloing was.  Trying to find groups as an Enchanter these days in the KEI era is frustrating, and lately I've been playing my Bard more.
<br />

<br />
I'll likely retire my Enchanter when he gets to 61 so that a very dear Coercer friend and guildie who always graciously buffs the rest of the guild with KEI can enjoy free KEI for the alts on the same account as her Enchanter.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=824212" target="_blank" class="postlink">Provender Moonshadow</a>, High Elf Phantasmist
