                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I don't mean to offend, but gg_prexus is exactly what I am ranting about.  Let me pull a couple quotes...
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>gg_prexus wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote"> No, but it does mean that  newer players have an easier time leveling.
<br />

<br />
The game was harder pre-sol,sorry thats just a fact. 
<br />

<br />
* Levels 35,40,45,50, 55, and 59 used to take a lot more exp to work through. A mob that gave you half a blue of exp in a non-hell level would only give you a pixels worth of exp in a hell-level.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
I think I pulled a fair sample, and did not mis-representing you.  Apologies if I did.  In addition, when I am saying, "you", I am referring to you and all those who share your expressed opinion, not as a personal attack.  Fair enough?
<br />

<br />
What "game" are you talking about?  Are you talking about the "game" you played way back when?  That game no longer exists.  No one is there.  Gaining levels in a group is easy, but there are no groups at low levels anymore (overstatement, but close).  So, the new player has the various advantages you listed, but has to do it solo, which is significantly more difficult.
<br />

<br />
So -- to make the point clearly:
<br />

<br />
1.  The "olde" game = some things that were more difficult + some things that were easier.
<br />

<br />
2.  The "current" game = some things that are more difficult + some things that are easier.
<br />

<br />
My rant is that folks who say things like, "The game was harder pre-sol,sorry thats just a fact" conveniently leave out the differences that make it harder now.
<br />

<br />
I was not there for the "olde" days, and those that were can't experience the current situation for the new player.  (I started a 2nd chanter on another server, and, with only my six month store of game knowledge, it was much easier -- so I am convinced that you can't re-live it.)  So, neither of us can really judge which of us had it easier.  Why is it that you claim to be able to do so?
<br />

<br />
This is not me defending my competence, or attacking yours.  I think I do very well, as, I'm sure, do most who take the time to read up on their class (like at "the runes").  I usually outperform other enchanters on raids, and regularly get compliments (and accusations of insanity) from those who have enchanter mains.  But, I'm not God's gift to enchanting, and there are things I've never done.  I'd empty my bank (mostly copper, so it's not a big deal...) to get into one of those uber xp Seb AE groups I've read about -- but no one is interested.  Again, illustrating the differences -- easier in some ways, harder in others...
<br />

<br />
Meschaelene</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
