                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Some changes that make the game "easier"
<br />

<br />
Pacify has killed the chanter's role in dungeon crawls.  Most groups refuse to pull more than 1 mob at a time if there is a cleric/paladin/ench in the group who can pacify. Bards/ench have all but killed the monk class.
<br />

<br />
Few new players understand agro radii, and pulling etc anymore.  They prefer to instead just waste mana trying to pacify every mob in the room before pulling that one next to the door which would come single or 1 add anyway.
<br />

<br />
Group exp bonuses. Literally exp 2x as fast killing the same mobs as 2yrs ago.
<br />

<br />
Gear.  For 5k you can outfit yourself in a decent set of HP gear.  For another 10-20k you can get yourself same fancy blades (melee) and almost double the dps your character would have had 2 yrs ago.
<br />

<br />
Platinum.  Is far easier to obtain; I remember being level 4 or 5 when I got my first platinum coin, saving every rat whiskey and snake skin.  I rolled a new bard on a new server, I had over 50pp, all my spells and instruments by level 5 killing yard trash.  Freeport yard trash has mobs that drop loots worth 1-3pp
<br />

<br />
Bags.  Every character starts with an 8 slot bag, this is a HUGE advantage because you can start your plat farming at level 1, instead of at whatever level you manage to forage enough to buy your first bag.  ALSO, the increased bank space helps all packrat players who save anything they think might be quest related.
<br />

<br />
Buffs.  Not counting the middle generation of level 1 KEI babies, buffs especially the cleric HP buff are still super powerful.
<br />

<br />
Rez's.  Remember, making the 20min run at level 16 from your bind to your camp?  Not anymore, cause clerics can start 0% rez, and the graduations between 0-50 and 90 are alot smoother.
<br />

<br />
Travel.  Try doing the Wind of Tashani quest without using pok books or Nexus. Also, try doing the stein of moggok (chanter right of passage) without using newer forms of travel.
<br />

<br />
Binds.  Melee characters can bind easily in many more zones than was previously available.  Little effect for casters.  Classic example would be the barbarian warrior who now can bind at the wayfarer camp, right next to his slaughter area.
<br />

<br />
Twink groups.  Gone are the days of trying to teach 5 others how to work with a chanter, usually. Also, these characters tend to have the best gear money can buy, and the best buffs their mains and other bots can provide.  They tend to group still for exp bonus and because they miss the social nature of the game.
<br />

<br />
What's harder?
<br />
Groups are harder to find.
<br />
Play skill in said groups is argueably lower because of previously mentioned advantages.
<br />

<br />
Now despite how unbalanced my list seems,  I am not going to pass judgement.  Like everyone else here, I know some very skilled "noobs" and I know some very dumb "vets".  But, after looking through my list, I can understand why some Vets feel the way they do.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=293448" target="_blank" class="postlink">Abitoo</a>
<br />
<a href="http://www.odysseysxev.com/" target="_blank" class="postlink">Odysseys</a> of Xev</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
