                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">But here's the argument that it's harder now. Other people here have written that, in the "olde" days, it was not "worth it" to use charm or charm solo. Now, even after the charm nerfs, and the group xp bonuses, and the "theoretically" better twinks that may populate your group, I had to level up with charm solo. So, it wasn't worth it then, and it has been heavily nerfed, but it's now worth it. If you think about it, this says a lot about groups and the new player's experience.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Simply put, charming 3 years ago was harder for the vast majority of enchanters.  Without easily available rezzes, most of us would go without.  With low HPs, we died more often.  Eventually, new equipment allowed the risk for charming to drop.
<br />

<br />
Eventually the very top end equipment allowed some enchanters to do insane things with charm with little risk.  Or, some unbelievable stuff (such as soloing Wuoshi) regardless of risk.  The risk was increased (affecting all charmers, including the non-elite), and the reward was decreased (again, for all charmers).  Collective punishment, if you will.
<br />

<br />
Overall, it has become safer, mainly due to increased durability of enchanters and is a way to earn some experience, if you have the talent.  I created a new character on Magelo that reflects what I had at lvl 39 (my heyday of charm soloing).  See <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=928987." target="_blank">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=928987.</a>  I had 600 HPs and 1500 Mana, with 122 charisma (unbuffed).
<br />

<br />
If you want to feel superior to old school enchanters, go for it.  If you want to consider and treat us as dinosaurs, that is your choice.  We learned differently, and having put 4 years into my character, I'm pretty sure I have a different feel for the class than those who have played less than a year.  Not better, different.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=37024" target="_blank" class="postlink">Serius</a>, Enchanter to King Tearis Thex on the Luclin Server
