                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Thanks Mesch for not taking anything as an attack, nothing I've said has been meant to offend, just commentary. The game has changed but it's still eq.
<br />

<br />
The argument can go around and around for ages. Abitoo and Seris have brought up many points since my last post that are very valid but you don't want to give them any weight. No one is saying that you are a poor player and no one is saying that you have everything handed to you on a silver platter. There are new difficulties that the olde school players but really the only ones I can think of are:
<br />

<br />
1. The expectations of  players to know "things". IE A friend of mine ( a newer player) complained in a raid that the enc wasn't mezzing the giants in kael. He was unmercifully educated real fast. Older players tend to look at everyone not 65 with a million aa as a twink, the idea of a REAL new player is an alien concept to some.
<br />

<br />
2. The lack of low level characters. This is the real hardship of new players. I have a mid 20's pally who had to solo his way to where he is so I could even think about getting a ldon group or any group. Most low level alts are powerleveled to 50-65 in a few days so I feel for the newer players on this point.
<br />

<br />
I'm sitting here at work writing/rewriting this trying to figure out how to explain my point best. The individaul specifics can be debated back and forth so lets go to a broader view. The game of Everquest back in '99/'00 was an unbalanced bug-ridden game. The design of the game was good but there were glaring flaws in the game that made things tougher than they are now. As the game advanced bugs were fixed, classes were rebalanced, content redesigned, content was added, new features were put in and old bad  features were removed ( hell levels and exp penalties).
<br />

<br />
Overall the game is easier but it is also more enjoyable. There was a time when I would never have considered making an alt, I went through the hell of leveling up my enc and never wanted to go through it again. The changes, however, have made making an alt more appealing. This is what SoE wanted, players to go back and start new characters and keep paying a monthly fee instead of "beating" the game with their main and quitting.
<br />

<br />
An example of then vs now. A minor one with a fairly large impact.
<br />

<br />
Then
<br />
My first character was an Erudite Wizard. Erudites are nightblind and start in a newbie area that is very very dark. I used to have to play with the lights out and my gamma turned to 100% just to SEE and even then it wasn't good clear vision. I used to run up against trees and not know because I COULDN'T SEE THE TREE. I did learn to love /loc from this experience and ever since I have a loc hotkey on the first page of my hotkey bank.  The entrance tunnel to Surefall Glade? Humans/Erudites/Barbarians used to get lost in that tunnel and would need to be led by the hand to get out. This is not a joke, my brother (HE Ranger who started in SFG) helped many people while snickering softly at them, me included.
<br />

<br />
Now.
<br />
The nightblindness is not nearly as bad. You don't have to turn off the lights and turn the gamma up. An Erudite can see the tree he is about to run into and won't spend the next 4 minutes wondering why it's taking so long to get to the beach.
<br />

<br />
1 small change that made the game much easier for many players.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">But here's the argument that it's harder now. Other people here have written that, in the "olde" days, it was not "worth it" to use charm or charm solo. Now, even after the charm nerfs, and the group xp bonuses, and the "theoretically" better twinks that may populate your group, I had to level up with charm solo. So, it wasn't worth it then, and it has been heavily nerfed, but it's now worth it. If you think about it, this says a lot about groups and the new player's experience. 
<br />
</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Pathing used to be atrocious. I mean horrible beyond belief. Imagine you pet is to your side ( NE corner of you i believe) and you are in a dungeon , Sola for example. You sidestep to the left 1 step and your pet goes off running through the dungeon trying to get back to your side and bringing back "friends". Pathing was sooo bad many times pet users were told they couldn't use pets. The pathing now is 1000x times better than it was which makes charm/pets more viable in more places.
<br />

<br />
The game is easier now, sorry thats just a fact. You weren't there so you really can't imagine what it was like.  Yes, you do have difficulties that the old players didn't but the changes that make the game easier far outweigh the newer difficulties. This doesn't mean you can't be or aren't a good player.
<br />

<br />
Here is another example of how SoE will change things to make them easier, it's not that old even. To get into BoT you used to have to kill the Lords ( AoW class mobs) at the giant forts for the quest pieces. Soon they changed it so that the quest pieces were on the mini's making it easier for players to gain entrance and progress. The old vs new argument came up over that when SoE decided to remove  flag requirements for certain zones. The "old" players that killed the Lords for their quest pieces were the most upset that "newer" players were getting free access to what "old " players worked so hard for.
<br />

<br />
Why did they change it? So people can continue to level and progress and keep on paying 13$ a month.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">You also did not have death helping you convince your group members to assist! </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Bullshit. Absolute bullshit.
<br />

<br />
The game is easier now, If you feel that takes away from sense of accomplishment then thats on you.
<br />

<br />
ps. You know how a mob's name flashes when you target them? Making it easy to see which mob you have targetted? Take a guess......</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Geaine Goldenspell
<br />
SoF-Prexus</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
