                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Seriusluclin wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Simply put, charming 3 years ago was harder for the vast majority of enchanters.  Without easily available rezzes, most of us would go without.  With low HPs, we died more often.  Eventually, new equipment allowed the risk for charming to drop.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
That is baloney, at least for pre-50's.
<br />

<br />
I charm soloed without resurrections in Mistmoore from 24-32 and in Kaesora from 36-43 wearing an almost full set of Artkeeper's Initiate armor and cloth armor in non-questable slots.  The newbie quest armor, at least for High Elves, is only marginally better than cloth or raw silk.
<br />

<br />
I agree that, if you buy gear to make it easier today, you can make it easier.  However, this equipment did <span style="font-weight: bold">not</span> enable charm soloing.  Enchanters have always been able to charm solo and actually were penalized less for doing so in the past.  The risk was a bit higher, but so was the reward.
<br />

<br />
Anyone who knew how to play a Necromancer back in the early days of EQ knows <span style="font-weight: bold">exactly</span> what I am talking about (i.e., level 45-50 necromancers soloing Lower Guk undead spots).</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=824212" target="_blank" class="postlink">Provender Moonshadow</a>, High Elf Phantasmist
