                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">That may be one of the biggest differences between old enchanters and new enchanters.  
<br />

<br />
Newer enchanters seem to refer to being good as charming or charm soloing.
<br />

<br />
Older enchanters refer to being good as the ability to lock down mobs.
<br />

<br />
I find that enchanters are the sum of their experiences and what they've learned from them.  The game has brushed aside some of the experiences that were around in the early days.  You can still seek out challenges that will make you better, but I guess the point is that a lot of people don't seek them out.  Quite frankly, seeking out challenges before level 60 these days is an ineffecient way to advance your character.
<br />

<br />
I'd guess that a lot of the bitching by older enchanters is just blaming new enchanters whenever a tank asks, "Is a 2 pull ok?"  
<br />
There seem to be more bad enchanters out there just based on the lowered expectations that we seem to get from groups.  
<br />

<br />
They may be powerleveled by people who've played the game for 4 years, they may be new players or they could be characters that were BoT'd to 60.
<br />

<br />
I really don't know if there are more bad enchanters now than before because I have very rarely grouped or been around other enchanters.  I do know that people's expectations for enchanters has been lowered, but at least it's not as bad as the low expectations for clerics.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
