                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I've seen a lot of people in this thread (not everyone, but some) confusing tedious with difficult.  A couple of examples: The boats were tedious, but they didn't make any part of the game more difficult.  Hell levels were tedious, but when they smoothed them out, the total amount of experience you needed to level didn't change -- the net effect was nothing but to reduce the discouragement of those handful of levels.
<br />

<br />
Certainly, there are a lot of things that are legitimately easier now, but let's not think that every one of these changes had a real effect on difficulty, per se, any more than Minotaur Hero Brews (a 9-item brewing combine with all vendor-bought materials) is actually more difficult than all of those 2-item JC combines.
<br />

<br />
There are talented enchanters of all vintages (and idiots as well), and we're all products of the era that we grew up in.  But one thing hasn't changed -- the rest of the world is full of morons that make our jobs harder.  <img src="images/smiles/icon_biggrin.gif" alt="icon_biggrin.gif" border="0" /></span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Sage Velurian Soliqui, E'ci
<br />
65 Enchanter &lt;Destruction of Authority&gt;
